{
  "text": "SDS-solubilized muscle fibers were run on an 8% SDS gel and transferred to a PVDF membrane for the Western blot analysis. The ImageJ software was used for densitometric analysis of protein bands in the Western blot. The total optical band intensity (i.e., the total amount of RcTnT in a single lane) was assumed to be the sum of the optical band intensities of both the endogenous RcTnT and the incorporated RcTnT (RcTnT WT , RcTnT 1-43\ue044 , or RcTnT 44-73\ue044 ) bands. The extent of incorporation was determined by dividing the optical band intensity of the exogenously added RcTnT with the total band intensity. This approach permitted us to precisely estimate the level of incorporation of different proteins in reconstituted fibers. In fibers from normal rats (\ue061-MHC), the level of incorporation was as follows: 80% for RcTnT WT (lane 2 of Fig. 2 B) , 99% for RcTnT 1-43\ue044 (lane 3 of Fig. 2 B) , and 80% for RcTnT 44-73\ue044 (lane 4 of Fig. 2 B) . The level of Figure 2 . SDS-PAGE analysis of MHC isoform expression and Western blot analysis of reconstituted fibers. Solubilized muscle fiber samples from normal (\ue061-MHC) and PTU-treated (\ue062-MHC) rat hearts were run on a 6% SDS gel to estimate the isoform levels of MHC [CITATION_1] . (A) SDS gel showing the isoform expression of MHC in the left ventricles of normal and PTU-treated rats. Rats fed on a PTU diet show a near-complete shift to \ue062-MHC isoform. (B) Western blot analysis of samples from reconstituted fibers expressing \ue061-MHC. Reconstituted fibers were solubilized using 2% SDS . Solubilized samples were run on an 8% SDS gel and transferred onto a PVDF membrane for Western blot analysis. Lane 1, purified recombinant RcTnT protein; lanes 2-4, samples from RcTnT WT -, RcTnT 1-43\ue044 -, and RcTnT 44-73\ue044 -reconstituted fibers. Molecular weights of proteins are indicated in parentheses. -activated maximal tension in fibers containing \ue062-MHC. RcTnT 1-43\ue044 decreased maximal tension by \ue07a46% in \ue061-MHC fibers, whereas RcTnT 1-43\ue044 decreased maximal tension by only 18% in \ue062-MHC fibers. Number of determinations was at least 13 for each group. Values are reported as mean \u00b1 SEM. ***, P < 0.001. To examine whether the effect of RcTnT 1-43\ue044 on maximal tension was caused by changes in the number of strongly bound XBs, we measured E D by imposing steplike length perturbations in constantly activated muscle fibers [CITATION_2] . The amplitude of the MLinduced instantaneous force (see F 1 in Fig. 4 and Fig. S1 ) increases with the amount of stretch and with the level of Ca 2+ activation because it is an approximate function of the number of force-bearing XBs. Therefore, a comparison of F 1 in Fig. 4 (A and B) suggests that the number of strongly bound XBs is attenuated more in \ue061-MHC + RcTnT 1-43\ue044 fibers. E D was estimated as described in Fig. 4 and Fig. S1 . Two-way ANOVA revealed a significant interaction effect (P < 0.001), suggesting a divergent impact of \ue061-and \ue062-MHC isoforms on how RcTnT 1-43\ue044 or hand, both \ue061-and \ue062-MHC isoforms did not alter Ca 2+ -activated maximal tension in RcTnT 44-73\ue044 fibers (Fig. 3,  A and B) . Ca 2+ -activated maximal ATPase activity was measured in reconstituted fibers at pCa 4.3. Two-way ANOVA revealed a significant interaction effect (P < 0.01), demonstrating a divergent impact of \ue061-and \ue062-MHC isoforms on how RcTnT 1-43\ue044 or RcTnT 44-73\ue044 affected Ca Step-like length perturbation protocol was as described previously [CITATION_3] . F 1 , F ss , and F nss are described in the supplemental text. Values are reported as mean \u00b1 SEM. ***, P < 0.001; **, P < 0.01. factor for the significant interaction effect on pCa 50 was caused by the divergent effects of \ue061-and \ue062-MHC isoforms on pCa 50 in RcTnT 1-43\ue044 versus RcTnT 44-73\ue044 fibers.",
